    "costs": "2500",
    "actions_taken": [
      "Updating JSA to include removal and verification of removal of pad eyes from RBC connector",
      "Updating Job By Design to move crew further back under safe area",
      "Evaluating if a DROPS shed is needed",
      "Reviewing potential DROPS area with all crews",
      "Exploring OEM change in coating color of pad eyes and evaluating ability to engineer out the need for pad eyes"
    ],
    "summary": "On April 26, 2021 at 0100 hours, while conducting well operations on the H&P 205 rig located on Perdido Spar in AC 857, a swivel pad eye mounted on a Drill Quip Radial Bolt Connector (RBC) contacted a trolley beam during lifting of the BOP double ram. The contact caused the swivel pad eye's mounting Allen bolt to shear, allowing the pad eye to separate into four pieces and fall 26 feet to the deck below. The 5.9 lbs lifting pad eye ring landed within 2 feet of a crewmember. Total damage was $2,500.",
    "recommendations": [
      "Update JSA to include removal and verification of removal of pad eyes from RBC connector",
      "Update Job By Design to move crew further back under safe area",
      "Evaluate if a DROPS shed is needed",
      "Review potential DROPS area with all crews",
      "Explore OEM change in coating color of pad eyes to improve visibility and/or engineer out the need for pad eyes on the RBC"
    ],
    "key_phrases": [
      "dropped object",
      "swivel pad eye",
      "Allen bolt shear",
      "trolley beam contact",
      "visibility issue",
      "tight tolerance",
